# Project source of truth

Product and architecture for this repo are defined in Linear:

**[CLAUDE.md — HAS Design Blog Agent Briefing](https://linear.app/iliketobuild/document/claudemd-has-design-blog-agent-briefing-5f16dbea3f75)**

Follow that document for what to build, what to remove, routes, content, CSS architecture, and constraints. Work the **HAS-D Blog** backlog in dependency order (starting with **ILI-561**) and satisfy each issue’s **Definition of Done** before marking it complete.

## Non-negotiables (must match Linear)

Do not contradict the briefing:

- **Text-only Astro blog.** Typography is the design (Gwern-like: minimal chrome, reading-first serif prose, monochrome + one link accent). No decorative UI.
- **No Three.js / WebGL / canvas / diorama** — remove all of it; do not preserve or extend.
- **No Tailwind** (remove integration). **Vanilla CSS only**, tokenized under `src/styles/` (`fonts.css`, `colors.css`, `typography.css`, `spacing.css`, `base.css`, `prose.css`) — no hardcoded colors/font sizes outside tokens.
- **No React, Vue, animation libraries, or third-party UI kits.** Astro components, static HTML, vanilla CSS.
- **No extra client JS** beyond what Astro’s build needs.
- **v1:** no images (text-only); self-hosted fonts in `public/fonts/` (no Google Fonts CDN). Two fonts max after ILI-561.
- **Routes (target):** `/` index, `/[slug]` articles, `/dev/type` and `/dev/prose` for dev tooling — plus excluding drafts from published queries as specified.

If repo files or `docs/` disagree with the above, **the Linear briefing wins**; update or remove stale files.

## Repo baseline (implementation)

The tree is intended to **match** this briefing: `articles` content collection, tokenized CSS under `src/styles/`, two-column shell, self-hosted fonts under `public/fonts/`, no Tailwind/Three/diorama, `/dev/type` and `/dev/prose` omitted from **production** builds. Future Linear issues **refine** this baseline—do not reintroduce the canceled stack.

## Deployments

Production deploys via **Vercel** (GitHub integration). **Production branch must be `main` in the Vercel project settings.** Merge PRs to **`main`** to ship.

## Git: `main` vs `dev` (read this before you touch anything)

**`main` and `dev` can diverge.** Different PR targets (some merged to `main`, some to `dev`) produced **two different lines of history** with different pixels (e.g. fonts on `main` vs ILI-570/571 only on `dev`). An agent (or human) on the wrong branch will “fix” the wrong tree and make everything worse.

**Before claiming branches match or before a release:**

```bash
git fetch origin && git rev-parse origin/main origin/dev
```

If the SHAs differ, **`main` and `dev` are not aligned** — merge or rebase until they match, then push both.

**Do not tell the user “aligned to main” unless those two refs are identical after `fetch`.**

## Tooling

Run **`npm`**, **Node**, and **Astro** (`npm run dev`, `npm run build`, `npm run check`, `npm install`) in whatever environment works for the task (local shell, CI, agent sandbox). **Docker Compose is optional** for local dev if `docker-compose.yml` exists — it is **not** required by project policy.

When implementing, **execute changes in the repo**; do not offload work to the user with checklists unless they explicitly want guidance only.
